OL,3,CWoman who survived stroke at 24 says
OL,4,Csinging helped her speak again
OL,6,F"She didn't know who I was at first,
OL,7,Fbut she could sing Proud Mary word for
OL,8,Fword," said Linda. "Singing brought
OL,9,Fher back to us."
OL,11,FSummer spent nine months in hospital,
OL,12,Frelearning how to walk, read, and
OL,13,Fperform daily tasks. Throughout her
OL,14,Frecovery, music remained a lifeline.
OL,16,FNow, she is backing a new campaign by
OL,17,Fthe Stroke Association called
OL,18,FSing4Stroke, aimed at raising
OL,19,Fawareness and funds for those living
OL,20,Fwith the long-term effects of stroke.
